  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $d_n=p_{n+1}-p_n$, where $p_n$ is the $n$th prime. Let $h(x)$ be maximal such that for some $n<x$ the numbers $d_n,d_{n+1},\\ldots,d_{n+h(x)-1}$ are all distinct. Estimate $h(x)$. In particular, is it true that\\[h(x) >(\\log x)^c\\]for some constant $c>0$, and\\[h(x)=o(\\log x)?\\]",
